nested_items.name: PartitionKey
nested_items.description: Determines which shard in the stream the data record is assigned to. Partition keys are Unicode strings with a maximum length limit of 256 characters for each key. Amazon Kinesis Data Streams uses the partition key as input to a hash function that maps the partition key and associated data to a specific shard. Specifically, an MD5 hash function is used to map partition keys to 128-bit integer values and to map associated data records to shards. As a result of this hashing mechanism, all data records with the same partition key map to the same shard within the stream.

nested_items.name: base
nested_items.description: The base value designates how many tasks, at a minimum, to run on the specified capacity provider. Only one capacity provider in a capacity provider strategy can have a base defined. If no value is specified, the default value of 0 is used.

nested_items.description: Specifies whether to enable Amazon ECS managed tags for the task. For more information, see Tagging Your Amazon ECS Resources in the Amazon Elastic Container Service Developer Guide.

nested_items.name: EnableExecuteCommand
nested_items.description: Whether or not to enable the execute command functionality for the containers in this task. If true, this enables execute command functionality on all containers in the task.

nested_items.name: PlacementConstraints
nested_items.description: An array of placement constraint objects to use for the task. You can specify up to 10 constraints per task (including constraints in the task definition and those specified at runtime).

nested_items.name: type
nested_items.description: The type of constraint. Use distinctInstance to ensure that each task in a particular group is running on a different container instance. Use memberOf to restrict the selection to a group of valid candidates.

nested_items.name: expression
nested_items.description: A cluster query language expression to apply to the constraint. You cannot specify an expression if the constraint type is distinctInstance. To learn more, see Cluster Query Language in the Amazon Elastic Container Service Developer Guide.

nested_items.name: PlacementStrategy
nested_items.description: The placement strategy objects to use for the task. You can specify a maximum of five strategy rules per task.

nested_items.name: type
nested_items.description: The type of placement strategy. The random placement strategy randomly places tasks on available candidates. The spread placement strategy spreads placement across available candidates evenly based on the field parameter. The binpack strategy places tasks on available candidates that have the least available amount of the resource that is specified with the field parameter. For example, if you binpack on memory, a task is placed on the instance with the least amount of remaining memory (but still enough to run the task).

nested_items.name: field
nested_items.description: The field to apply the placement strategy against. For the spread placement strategy, valid values are instanceId (or host, which has the same effect), or any platform or custom attribute that is applied to a container instance, such as attribute:ecs.availability-zone. For the binpack placement strategy, valid values are cpu and memory. For the random placement strategy, this field is not used.

nested_items.name: VersionValue
nested_items.description: 64 bit version value or source data field that represents the version value for your data.

nested_items.name: DimensionMappings
nested_items.description: Map source data to dimensions in the target Timestream for LiveAnalytics table.

nested_items.name: DimensionValue
nested_items.description: Dynamic path to the dimension value in the source event.

nested_items.name: DimensionValueType
nested_items.description: The data type of the dimension for the time-series data.

nested_items.name: DimensionName
nested_items.description: The metadata attributes of the time series. For example, the name and Availability Zone of an Amazon EC2 instance or the name of the manufacturer of a wind turbine are dimensions.

nested_items.name: SingleMeasureMappings
nested_items.description: Mappings of single source data fields to individual records in the specified Timestream for LiveAnalytics table.

nested_items.name: MeasureValue

nested_items.name: MeasureValueType
nested_items.description: Data type of the source field.

nested_items.name: MeasureName
nested_items.description: Target measure name for the measurement attribute in the Timestream table.

nested_items.name: MultiMeasureMappings
nested_items.description: Maps multiple measures from the source event to the same record in the specified Timestream for LiveAnalytics table.

nested_items.name: MultiMeasureName
nested_items.description: The name of the multiple measurements per record (multi-measure).

nested_items.name: MultiMeasureAttributeMappings
nested_items.description: Mappings that represent multiple source event fields mapped to measures in the same Timestream for LiveAnalytics record.

nested_items.name: MeasureValue
nested_items.description: Dynamic path to the measurement attribute in the source event.

nested_items.name: MeasureValueType
nested_items.description: Data type of the measurement attribute in the source event.

nested_items.name: MultiMeasureAttributeName
nested_items.description: Target measure name to be used.

nested_items.description: The name of the Amazon S3 bucket to which EventBridge delivers the log records for the pipe.

nested_items.name: Prefix
nested_items.description: The prefix text with which to begin Amazon S3 log object names.

nested_items.name: BucketOwner
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services account that owns the Amazon S3 bucket to which EventBridge delivers the log records for the pipe.

nested_items.name: OutputFormat

nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services Resource Name (ARN) for the CloudWatch log group to which EventBridge sends the log records.

nested_items.name: Level
nested_items.description: The level of logging detail to include. This applies to all log destinations for the pipe.

nested_items.name: IncludeExecutionData
